    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Office of<lb/>
                J.D. Eisenstein&#44;<lb/>
                Manufacturer of<lb/>
                Ladies&#39; and Gents&#39; Underwear&#44;<lb/>
                57 East Broadway&#44;<lb/></p>
                
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93; New York&#44; April 8&#91;&#44;&#93; 1886<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais.<lb/>
                546 North 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Str.<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#58; &#45;&#45; שלום. Enclosed please find a <sic>clip&#45;<lb/> ing</sic>  from to&#45;days &#34;N.Y. Juedische Zeitung&#34; a continu&#45;<lb/>ation of an article concerning your movement about<lb/> the New Theological College&#44; written by my friend<lb/> Mr J. D. Eisenstein. Mr Eisenstein showed to me his M.S.S.<lb/> which will be published next week&#44; where I find the follow&#45;<lb/>ing sentence &#40;in his critic about the <sic>Pittsburg</sic> platform&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>I said to Mr E. that I cannot believe that you<lb/> shall have made such a declaration and I cannot<lb/> consider you as &#34;Conservative&#34; because you objected<lb/> to that name for the new movement and so far as<lb/> I know you I consider you as strict &#39;Orthodox&#39;<lb/> in the true sense of the word.		&#40;over&#41;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Mr E. says that he has this from good authority<lb/> and two of his friends told him the same story<lb/> in different times. Should you find it necessary to<lb/> explain before it is published please communicate<lb/> either to Mr E at the above address or to yours<lb/></p>
            <p>very obediently<lb/>
                J. Judelsohn<lb/>
                248 East Broadway&#44;<lb/>
                New York City.<lb/></p>
            <p>P.S. I don&#39;t know yet <sic>wether</sic> Mr E is in favor<lb/> of the movement or not&#44; but I am convinced<lb/> that most of our orthodox brethren and<lb/> congregations are favoring the movement and<lb/> they will give their hearty&#91;&#63;&#93; support in<lb/> due time&#45;&#45; Except this I am glad<lb/> to inform you that 5000 Jewish work&#45;<lb/>ingmen &#40;cloakmakers&#41; have succeeded in<lb/> their strike where you find among other<lb/> matters the following paragraph&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#34;No Jew or Jewess shall be<lb/>
                &#34; compelled to work on the<lb/>
                &#34;Jewish Sabbath or Holiday.<lb/></p>
            <p>and the Saturday half holiday movement among<lb/> non&#45;Jews will <sic>compell</sic> our rich co&#45;religionists<lb/> to close up on Saturday.<lb/></p>
            <p>My sincere regards to your beloved family.				J.J.<lb/></p>
                
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>If Not delivered in ten days&#44; return to<lb/>
                J.D.  EISENSTEIN&#44;<lb/>
                Manufacturer of<lb/>
                Ladies&#39; and Gents&#39; Underwear&#44;<lb/>
                57 EAST BROADWAY&#44;<lb/>
                New York&#44;<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev S. Morias<lb/>
                546 North 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Str<lb/>
                Philadelphia PA<lb/></p>
            </body>
